        <div class="col-xs-12">
            <h1 class="cd-text cd-title">icons</h1>
            <h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Loader</h2>
            <p class="cd-text">A general loading animation which can be used for any action that is waiting for a response to an in-page (ajax) request.</p>
            <p><span class="icon-loader"></span></p>
            <p><code>&lt;span class="icon-loader"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</code></p>

            <h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Font awesome icons</h2>
            <p class="cd-text">These are the font awesome icons that we use which cover most requirements. A full list can be found at <a href="https://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome/icons/">the font awesome site</a> but care should be taken to avoid using slightly different icons for the same function. Consistency is important.</p>
            <p class="cd-text">Never use an icon on it's own without either providing some visible text that explains the meaning. At the very least you should provide some <a href="http://pistachio.graze.com/components/utilities#accessibility-utilities">text for assistive devices</a> or a <a href="tooltips">tooltip</a></p>

